Yes — this can become a **personal life operating system** for you, not just a normal to-do app.

The goal should be: **one app that helps you remember, plan, act, track, and improve daily life.**

## 1. Daily Dashboard

This is the first screen when you open the app.

It should show:

| Section          | Purpose                                |
| ---------------- | -------------------------------------- |
| Today’s tasks    | What must be done today                |
| Calendar events  | Meetings, appointments, deadlines      |
| Bills due        | Rent, internet, electricity, gas, etc. |
| Health reminders | Water, sleep, exercise, medication     |
| Focus priority   | The one main thing for today           |
| Quick notes      | Capture thoughts fast                  |
| Mood/energy      | Track how you feel daily               |

Example:

> Today
> Main Focus: Finish Paysavo review
> Bills: Internet due tomorrow
> Habit: 30 min learning
> Reminder: Call mechanic at 5 PM

## 2. Task and Goal Management

Not just simple tasks. You need levels:

### Daily Tasks

Small things like:

> Pay bill
> Review PR
> Call someone
> Buy groceries

### Weekly Goals

Example:

> Finish one Laravel security topic
> Exercise 3 times
> Save 10,000 PKR
> Record 2 content videos

### Long-Term Goals

Example:

> Become stronger Laravel/PHP engineer
> Build Paysavo modules with better security
> Grow TikTok/YouTube content
> Manage personal finances better

Each goal should have:

| Field        | Example                                   |
| ------------ | ----------------------------------------- |
| Goal title   | Improve Laravel fundamentals              |
| Target date  | 30 June                                   |
| Progress     | 45%                                       |
| Linked tasks | Watch course, solve problems, review code |
| Notes        | Weak in testing and architecture          |

## 3. Smart Reminders

This should solve the problem of forgetting things.

Features:

| Reminder Type      | Example                        |
| ------------------ | ------------------------------ |
| One-time reminder  | Renew license tomorrow         |
| Repeating reminder | Pay rent every month           |
| Location reminder  | Buy groceries when near market |
| Urgent reminder    | Call client before 6 PM        |
| Follow-up reminder | Check if someone replied       |

Very useful feature:

> “Remind me if I have not completed this task by 8 PM.”

## 4. Personal Finance Manager

Since you already track expenses like rent, internet, electricity, this will be very useful.

Features:

| Feature           | Purpose                              |
| ----------------- | ------------------------------------ |
| Monthly expenses  | Track fixed bills                    |
| Daily spending    | Food, fuel, shopping                 |
| Income tracking   | Salary, freelance, side income       |
| Savings goal      | Save for laptop, car, emergency fund |
| Debt/loan tracker | Track borrowed/lent money            |
| Bill alerts       | Never miss due dates                 |

Example categories:

> Rent
> Internet
> Electricity
> Gas
> Mobile
> Fuel
> Food
> Family
> Business
> Learning

Important: use **minor-unit money internally** even for personal app finance. Store `150000` for PKR 1,500.00 instead of floating values.

